A plume of steam and ash rose from the crater of Mount St. Helens on Friday, CNN reported.
Soon afterward came confirmation that Mount St. Helens had erupted for the first time since 1986.
Before 1980, Mount St. Helens had last erupted in 1857.
Volcanic experts have been warning of a possible imminent eruption of Mount St Helens for several days as seismic activity in the area grew.
That suddenly created a more serious situation at Mount St. Helens, the most active volcano in the lower 48 states.
Seismometers pinpoint the tiny earthquakes that have been shaking Mount St. Helens for the past week and a half.
